[p 
	"In this storybook-view RPG, the author zooms around the game world, entering the most dangerous of dungeons, killing two powerful monsters, and collecting the bare minimum needed to beat the game in incredible fashion. Despite the player being 
	[em 
		[a class=extlink href=http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OneHitPointWonder rel=nofollow 
			"unable to survive one hit
		]a
	]em
	", the author subverts certain death with the handy pause system. Despite the player supposedly being unable to damage the monsters, an underflow glitch allows for massive damage. Despite the final boss standing right there to kill him, the viewer sees all of 3 frames of the dark overlord. It's an RPG done in just over one minute, without warping or save glitching.
	$LF
